and nighttime levels 28.1% (95% CI: À42.3% to À10.4%) and 22.9% lower (95% CI: À39.3% to À3.0%), respectively. Obese individuals had 31.6% (95% CI: À47.8% to À10.4%), 31.6% (95% CI: À48.8% to À8.6%), and 30.9% (95% CI: À47.3% to À9.5%) lower 24-h, daytime, and nighttime BNP levels compared with lean individuals, respectively (Table 3). Similarly, compared with lean individuals,

